custom exceptions are user-defined exceptions created for the business specific errors

how to create a custom exception?
by extending Exception or run-time-exception

Difference between Checked and Unchecked Custom Exceptions?
| Checked            | Unchecked                |
| ------------------ | ------------------------ |
| Extends Exception  | Extends RuntimeException |
| Compile Time       | Runtime                  |
| Mandatory Handling | Optional Handling        |

CUSTOM EXCEPTION

Definition:
User-defined exception created for
business-specific validations.

Creation:
class MyException extends Exception

Types:
1. Checked  -> extends Exception
2. Unchecked -> extends RuntimeException

Keywords:
throw  -> create exception object
throws -> delegate handling

Benefits:
✔ Readability
✔ Business Rules
✔ Better Debugging
✔ Maintainability

Common Examples:
InvalidAgeException
InvalidSalaryException
InvalidMarksException
InsufficientBalanceException
InvalidPinException